> direction, I reach a certain point
> in turning the steering wheel, and
> there is a "give point".

> turn wheel...  feel "bump" in wheel,
> keep turning, bump is gone.  I feel
> "bump" while turning back past
> that point as well.

My long-distance diagnosis is a bad steering worm in the steering gearbox.
Only fix is to replace the gearbox.  If it's bumpy, you're beyond the
point of adjusting the problem away.

You need a 68-72 worm-and-peg gearbox.  The 73-up box won't fit.

George
